The latest British opinion poll, gaveMargaret Thatcher's Conservatives a 17-point lead over theopposition -- the highest rating yet for the Prime Minister whois seeking a record third consecutive term.    The poll in today's Sun tabloid showed the Conservativescould win a majority of 125 seats in Parliament in the nextgeneral elections. Thatcher must call the elections by June1988, but is expected to do so this year. The survey, conductedbetween April 10 and 12 among 1,000 adults eligible to vote,gave the Conservatives 44 pct, and left-wing Labour and thecentrist Liberal-Social Democratic Alliance 27 pct each.&#3;